[SN]TITLE[SN]
The Syrians in Beirut who are staying put

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A quarter of people living in Lebanon are now refugees - many of them Syrians. Thousands have applied for asylum in the West, but many want to stay where they are.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
18 April 2016 Last updated at 00:29 BST
The BBC's Lina Sinjab spoke to four Syrians in the Lebanese capital, Beirut, who have no intention of going further afield.
An artist, an actor, an aid worker and a singer tell of their experiences.
